WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.280
Are you looking for some good agent skills to help you with your coding?

00:00:03.280 --> 00:00:05.520
Check out the skills repo from PositDev.

00:00:05.520 --> 00:00:09.880
The PositDevs have created a ton of agent skills that can help you with your development

00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:10.880
process.

00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:16.000
With the critical code reviewer skill, your LLM acts as a senior engineer conducting rigorous

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.320
adversarial code review with zero tolerance for mediocrity.

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:23.320
There's a Cordo authoring skill to help you with things like adding citations and editing

00:00:23.320 --> 00:00:26.920
YAML, and it also helps you migrate from R Markdown to Cordo too.

00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:31.360
And if you do a lot of R package development, there's a skill for that with DevTools, TestFad,

00:00:31.360 --> 00:00:32.360
and Roxygen.

00:00:32.360 --> 00:00:34.680
There are a bunch more in the repo, definitely go check them out.

